---
/**
 * Guided walk — Chapter 4 of 5: "What it costs the public". The first fully-built
 * chapter; the proven template for the rest. Narrative prose braided with the
 * Record Teardown teaching component (the Tetra Tech OPC, then the RDA), a
 * transferable-skill takeaway, and exits back into the reference library.
 */
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import PathWayfinding from "../../components/PathWayfinding.astro";
import RecordTeardown from "../../components/RecordTeardown.astro";
import { OPC_TEARDOWN, RDA_TEARDOWN } from "../../lib/teardowns";
import { chapterByStep, WALK_INDEX_HREF, walkHref } from "../../lib/walk";
import { withBase } from "../../lib/site";

const STEP = 4;
const prev = chapterByStep(STEP - 1);
const next = chapterByStep(STEP + 1);
---

<Base
  title="What it costs the public — Chapter 4"
  section="site"
  description="The public's share of the data-center project arrives as roads, booked as a private gift. Read the cost estimate and the agreement that prices it."
>
  <div class="walk-chapter-page">
    <PathWayfinding step={STEP} />

    <div class="walk-chapter-eyebrow">Chapter {STEP} of 5 · the guided walk</div>
    <h1 class="walk-chapter-h1">What it costs the public</h1>

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        The public's share of this project arrives as roads — four roundabouts and
        two corridor rebuilds, dedicated to the county to maintain in perpetuity,
        and booked in the agreement that authorizes them as a <em>private</em>
        contribution from the developer. The estimate that sets the price is a Tetra
        Tech <strong>Opinion of Probable Cost</strong>. Read it the way an engineer
        would: start from the total, then ask what the total leaves out.
      </p>
    </div>

    <RecordTeardown record={OPC_TEARDOWN} layout="split" />

    <div class="td-beat">
      <div class="td-beat-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</div>
      <div class="td-beat-text">
        <b>and then —</b> that $14.2M estimate becomes a “private” contribution in
        the deal itself, where the clauses decide who really pays.
      </div>
    </div>

    <RecordTeardown record={RDA_TEARDOWN} layout="split" />

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        Read together, the two records say the same thing twice: a public-works
        number precise to the dollar sitting on a scope thin enough to hide a
        floodplain, wrapped in a contract whose quiet clauses decide who actually
        carries the cost.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout walk-takeaway">
      <p class="callout-title">What you can read anywhere now</p>
      <p>
        An <strong>Opinion of Probable Cost</strong> — check for the design-storm
        basis and whether detention is shown; their absence on a drainage line is a
        scope gap, not a rounding error. And a <strong>development agreement</strong>
        — the clauses on grant-refunds, records-notice, and competitive procurement
        are where the public's leverage is kept or quietly given away.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="walk-explore-h">Explore this in the library</h2>
    <div class="doors">
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/site/records/")}>
        <span class="door-label">The OPC record</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The full extraction — every roundabout's line items and subtotals.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/site/legal/")}>
        <span class="door-label">Legal history</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The Roadwork Development Agreement and the resolutions that adopted it.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/docs/economics")}>
        <span class="door-label">The economics</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The abatement and public-cost picture the roadwork sits inside.</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <nav class="walk-nav" aria-label="Chapter navigation">
      {
        prev?.live ? (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev" href={walkHref(prev.slug)}>← {prev.step}. {prev.title}</a>
        ) : prev ? (
          <span class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev is-disabled" title="Drafting">← {prev.step}. {prev.title}</span>
        ) : (
          <span></span>
        )
      }
      <a class="walk-nav-leave" href={WALK_INDEX_HREF}>All chapters</a>
      {
        next?.live ? (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-next" href={walkHref(next.slug)}>{next.step}. {next.title} →</a>
        ) : next ? (
          <span class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-next is-disabled" title="Drafting">{next.step}. {next.title} →</span>
        ) : (
          <span></span>
        )
      }
    </nav>
  </div>
</Base>
